# segundo-cerebro — wiki rules

- **Human-only zones — immutable for the agent:** never edit, rename, move, or delete anything under **`A00 Inbox/`**, **`A01 Processamento/`**, **`A02 Anchor Topics/`**, **`A03 Banco de imagens/`**, **`A04 Daily Notes/`**, **`A05 Backlog/`**, **`C02 Readwise/`**, **`C03 Books database/`**, **`C05 Excalidraw/`**. Humans add sources and personal notes; agents only read when ingesting or answering.
- **Wiki (`B*`):** agent-maintained Markdown (+ Mermaid): create/update pages, wikilinks, `B05 Systems/overview.md`, `B05 Systems/index.md`, and append `B05 Systems/log.md` per workflow in `CLAUDE.md`.
- **Domain:** data science & AI engineering research notes from articles/videos.
- **Bilingual:** pt-BR body; EN for YAML keys, slugs/folders, standard technical terms, verbatim quotes; add “Termos (EN)” gloss when jargon-heavy.
- **Ingest:** **one new source per pass** unless the user explicitly requests batching. Propose takeaways → **wait for user confirmation** → then write wiki (typically 5–15 files).
- **Lint:** only when the user asks (contradictions, orphans, missing concepts, stale claims, broken links, next questions).
- **MVP outputs:** Markdown + Mermaid only; no Marp/matplotlib unless the user asks.
- **Navigation:** read `B05 Systems/index.md` first for queries; keep it updated after ingests and material explorations.
- **Schema:** if anything conflicts, follow `CLAUDE.md` as source of truth.
